<subSubSection id="8BFC654DFFE7FF8DFF507BC1FE974FA9" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C35936C6FFE7FF8DFF507BC1FE974FA9" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="F192EAD4FFE7FF8DFF507BC1FECF4E91" bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="04E64D45FFE7FF8DFED27BCFFDEE4E91" box="[325,538,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Metopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis id="F192EAD4FFE7FF8DFED27BCFFDEE4E91" box="[325,538,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Metopina obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to a group of species that also includes 
<taxonomicName id="04E64D45FFE7FF8DFBCF7BCFFA9B4E91" authority="Liu, 1995" authorityName="Liu" authorityYear="1995" box="[1112,1391,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Metopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamularis">
<emphasis id="F192EAD4FFE7FF8DFBCF7BCFFB064E91" box="[1112,1266,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">M. hamularis</emphasis>
Liu, 
<number id="752E24E1FFE7FF8DFAA37BC1FA9B4E91" box="[1332,1391,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="04E64D45FFE7FF8DFAEA7BCFFE8A4EF5" authority="Liu, 2012" authorityName="Liu" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Metopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundata">
<emphasis id="F192EAD4FFE7FF8DFAEA7BCFFEF04EF4" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">M. rotundata</emphasis>
Liu, 
<number id="752E24E1FFE7FF8DFED47BEAFE8A4EF5" box="[323,382,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="04E64D45FFE7FF8DFE1D7BEBFD364EF5" authority="Schmitz, 1927" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1927" box="[394,706,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Metopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventralis">
<emphasis id="F192EAD4FFE7FF8DFE1D7BEBFDE74EF4" box="[394,531,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">M. ventralis</emphasis>
Schmitz, 
<number id="752E24E1FFE7FF8DFD107BEAFD364EF5" box="[647,706,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="1927.0">1927</number>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="04E64D45FFE7FF8DFD687BEBFBB54EF4" authority="Disney, 2006" authorityName="Disney" authorityYear="2006" box="[767,1089,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Metopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanharteni">
<emphasis id="F192EAD4FFE7FF8DFD687BEBFC6B4EF4" box="[767,927,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">M. vanharteni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A7774B37FFE7FF8DFC307BEAFBB54EF4" author="Disney" box="[935,1089,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (2006) Scuttle flies (Diptera: Phoridae). Part I: all genera except Megaselia. Fauna of Arabia, 22, 473 - 521." type="journal article" year="2006">
Disney, 
<number id="752E24E1FFE7FF8DFB927BEAFBB54EF4" box="[1029,1089,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The female of each species is easily identifiable based on the structure of its tergite 
<number id="752E24E1FFE7FF8DFCB57B89FCC74ED9" box="[802,819,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="5.0">5</number>
. On the contrary, recognition of males may pose some difficulty, although they all are distinct in having a club- or sausage-like spine on the trochanter (
<figureCitation id="5BDD2A43FFE7FF8DFA9A7A52FA944F3D" box="[1293,1376,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1626,1648]" captionTargetBox="[327,1255,198,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[317,1269,193,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Posterior face of hind femur of Metopina males. 10, M. kuslitzkyi sp. n.; 11, M. obsoleta; 12, M. ulrichi. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number id="752E24E1FFE7FF8DFAD27A52FA944F3D" box="[1349,1376,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) and sclerotized plates on the abdominal venter. Males of 
<taxonomicName id="04E64D45FFE7FF8DFD7F7A7FFC984F61" box="[744,876,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Metopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis id="F192EAD4FFE7FF8DFD7F7A7FFC984F61" box="[744,876,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">M. obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="04E64D45FFE7FF8DFB3E7A7FFABC4F61" box="[1193,1352,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Metopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanharteni">
<emphasis id="F192EAD4FFE7FF8DFB3E7A7FFABC4F61" box="[1193,1352,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">M. vanharteni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from 
<collectingCountry id="BBF17656FFE7FF8DFF437A1AFE984F44" box="[212,364,332,357]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="4" pageNumber="65">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
; however, females of the former species immediately differ in the semilunar shape of their fifth abdominal tergite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
